HEADWORD: Excommunion
<hw>Ex`com*mun"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A shutting out from
communion; excommunication.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Excommunication</qex> is the utmost of ecclesiastical
judicature.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excoriable</ent>⟦br⟧
